@startuml C4_Ops_LoggingArchitecture
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Operations - Comprehensive Logging Architecture

Boundary(sources, "Log Sources") {
    Component(app_logs, "ApplicationLogs", "Code", "SLF4J logs")
    Component(request_logs, "RequestLogs", "HTTP", "Nginx access")
    Component(error_logs, "ErrorLogs", "Exceptions", "Stack traces")
    Component(audit_logs, "AuditLogs", "Events", "User actions")
}

Boundary(collection, "Collection Layer") {
    Component(filebeat, "Filebeat", "Agent", "Log collection")
    Component(fluent, "Fluent Bit", "Alternative", "Lightweight")
    Component(log_buffer, "LogBuffer", "Queue", "Buffering")
}

Boundary(pipeline, "Processing Pipeline") {
    Component(parser, "LogParser", "Transform", "JSON parsing")
    Component(enricher, "LogEnricher", "Context", "Add metadata")
    Component(filter, "LogFilter", "Selection", "Sensitive data")
}

Boundary(storage, "Storage") {
    Component(elasticsearch, "Elasticsearch", "Index", "Full-text search")
    Component(s3, "S3/GCS", "Archive", "Long-term storage")
}

Boundary(visualization, "Visualization & Analysis") {
    Component(kibana, "Kibana", "Dashboard", "Log exploration")
    Component(splunk, "Splunk", "Alternative", "Enterprise logging")
}

sources --> filebeat: Collects
filebeat --> log_buffer: Buffers
log_buffer --> parser: Parses
parser --> enricher: Enriches
enricher --> filter: Filters
filter --> elasticsearch: Indexes
elasticsearch --> s3: Archives
elasticsearch --> kibana: Powers dashboard

Note as N1
Logging Architecture:

Log Sources:
- Application: SLF4J (INFO, WARN, ERROR)
- HTTP: Nginx access/error logs
- Errors: Full stack traces + context
- Audit: User actions, API calls

Collection:
- Filebeat: Primary log collector
- Fluent Bit: Lightweight alternative
- Heartbeat: Health check logs
- Buffering: Prevent loss on spike

Pipeline:
- Parser: Convert to JSON
- Enricher: Add hostname, version, trace ID
- Filter: Remove sensitive data (PII)

Storage:
- Elasticsearch: Hot storage (current day)
- S3/GCS: Cold storage (>7 days)
- TTL: Keep for 90 days

Visualization:
- Kibana: Real-time exploration
- Pre-built dashboards: Errors, latency
- Alerts: Critical errors → PagerDuty

Log Levels:
- ERROR: System errors, must fix
- WARN: Potential issues, investigate
- INFO: Important events, track behavior
- DEBUG: Development only (not prod)

Log Format (JSON):
{
  "timestamp": "2026-03-04T12:34:56Z",
  "level": "ERROR",
  "logger": "YNetRunner",
  "message": "Task failed",
  "traceId": "abc-123",
  "userId": "user-456",
  "duration": 1234
}

SLA:
- Log delivery: <1 second
- Search latency: <5 seconds
- Retention: 90 days
- Availability: 99.9%

Optimization:
- Batch writing to Elasticsearch
- Compression in S3
- Sampling for high-volume logs
- Retention policies per log type
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
